  "prompt": "How can I troubleshoot a mouse that keeps freezing?",
  "response": "Here are some steps to troubleshoot a freezing mouse:\n\n1. Basic Checks\n- Check the mouse battery (if wireless)\n- Clean the mouse sensor with compressed air\n- Try a different USB port\n- Verify cable connections are secure\n\n2. Hardware Troubleshooting\n- Test the mouse on another computer\n- Try a different mouse on your computer\n- Check for physical damage to the mouse\n\n3. Software Solutions\n- Update mouse/touchpad drivers\n- Restart your computer\n- Check for conflicting software\n- Run a system update\n- Uninstall and reinstall mouse drivers\n\n4. For Wireless Mice\n- Replace batteries\n- Check wireless interference\n- Ensure proper distance from receiver\n- Verify receiver is functioning correctly\n\n5. Advanced Troubleshooting\n- Check system performance/resources\n- Scan for malware\n- Reset mouse settings\n- Disable mouse acceleration\n- Check for Windows mouse settings conflicts\n\n6. Consider Replacement\n- If all troubleshooting fails, the mouse might be defective\n- Consider purchasing a new mouse\n\nSpecific steps may vary depending on your operating system and mouse type.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these steps?",
